From: L'Electron Rare <contact@saillant.cc>
Subject: [PATCH] feat(config): KIKI_FLOW_ENABLED feature flag

Adds a single env-var-driven feature flag that gates kiki-flow
advisory integration in the MoE router. Default off. Enables
safe rollout and instant kill-switch without code changes.

This patch only introduces the plumbing; the actual router wiring
(importing StreamingRunner and blending advisory weights) depends
on resolution of Dep 3 (query-string plumbing) and is applied
separately.

Apply from ~/KIKI-Mac_tunner:
    cd ~/KIKI-Mac_tunner
    git apply /path/to/01-micro-kiki-dep4-feature-flag.patch
    git add src/config.py  # or wherever the Config dataclass lives
    git commit -m "feat(config): KIKI_FLOW_ENABLED feature flag (off by default)"

---
 src/config.py | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/config.py b/src/config.py
--- a/src/config.py
+++ b/src/config.py
@@ -1,6 +1,13 @@
 """Centralised configuration for micro-kiki services."""
 from __future__ import annotations

 import os
 from dataclasses import dataclass, field

+
+def _env_bool(name: str, default: bool = False) -> bool:
+    raw = os.environ.get(name)
+    if raw is None:
+        return default
+    return raw.strip().lower() in {"1", "true", "yes", "on"}
+
+
 @dataclass
 class Config:
     # ... (existing fields)
+    kiki_flow_enabled: bool = field(default_factory=lambda: _env_bool("KIKI_FLOW_ENABLED"))
